This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition and acoustic modeling using deep neural networks. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with audio signals and their processing. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new technique for normalizing the activities of neurons in deep neural networks. It could also be categorized under cs.SI (Signal Processing) as it deals with processing audio signals for speech recognition. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the use of neural networks for speech recognition.
